%N A039368 Numbers whose base-9 representation has the same nonzero number of 1's and 5's.
%H A039368 Chris R. Rehmann, <a href="/A039368/b039368.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%t A039368 Select[Range[1000], DigitCount[#, 9, 1]==DigitCount[#, 9, 5]>0&] (* _Chris R. Rehmann_, Apr 05 2026 *)
%o A039368 (MATLAB) x = 0:782; d = dec2base(x,9)-'0'; s1 = sum(d==1,2); s2 = sum(d==5,2); a = x(s1==s2 & s1>0); disp(regexprep(num2str(a), ' +', ', ')) % _Chris R. Rehmann_, Apr 05 2026
